President Biden delivered a speech at the Royal Air Force Mildenhall in the United Kingdom, thanking the military personnel and their families for their service and sacrifices. He highlighted the historical significance of the base and the strong bond between the United States and the United Kingdom. President Biden emphasized the importance of international partnerships and alliances, including NATO, in addressing global challenges such as climate change, cybersecurity, and COVID-19. He expressed the commitment of the United States to lead with strength and defend democratic values. President Biden also mentioned his upcoming meetings with world leaders, including Russian President Vladimir Putin, where he will reinforce the United States' position on strategic stability and human rights. He concluded by expressing his confidence in the American people's ability to strengthen democracy and overcome any challenges they face.